"free-falling" means when you're falling and no other forces but gravity is acting upon you. When you make a jump while you're IN the atmosphere, gravity is not the only force acting upon you, because there's also air-resistance, which allows you to reach what is known as "terminal velocity". The only way to free-fall is to do it in a vacuum, like Space. It's what astronauts, satellites, planets, stars and any other celestial bodies do.
